issue.title: ES6 and ES7 features in tests (import, export, async & await)
issue.body:
Let's bring in some ES6 and ES7 goodies to make the tests even easier to read, understand and write. The promises boilerplate replaced by async / await and requires replaced by ES6 imports / exports.

What do you think? Step in the right direction or nonsense?

comment.body: No, those changes and dependencies are just for the tests. Variety is still dependencies-free and standalone.

issue.title: Cannot use 'commands' readMode, degrading to 'legacy' mode
issue.body:
Hi everyone,
During testing of Variety, I hit following warning:

```
Cannot use 'commands' readMode, degrading to 'legacy' mode
```

It appears only when newer shell (3.2) is used for analysis against older database (lower than 3.0). There have been some changes in communication protocol introduced and this warning is produced only when fallback method used. 

The real problem for us is - **this warning cannot be muted** by ```--quiet``` option of mongo shell and thus **breaks JSON output**.  

To address this issue, I've created following pull request: https://github.com/mongodb/mongo/pull/1073. It has also its own Jira Issue: https://jira.mongodb.org/browse/SERVER-21745

Could you please upvote the issue or write a comment, to get things in motion? 

Thank you!
Tomas

comment.body: Hi Arthur, exactly - even with ```--quiet```. Could you please [upvote the jira issue](https://jira.mongodb.org/browse/SERVER-21745) too?
